# Admin Portal Implementation Commands
# Add these rules to your .cursorrules file

## Parent Command: /implement-admin-portal

When user executes `/implement-admin-portal`:
1. Show overview from `documentation/admin/00-IMPLEMENTATION-GUIDE.md`
2. List all 15 epics with status
3. Ask which epic to start
4. Execute corresponding child command

## Child Commands (Epic Implementation)

### /admin-01-authentication
Epic 1: Authentication & Access Control
- Read: `documentation/admin/01-EPIC-Authentication.md`
- Stories: AUTH-001 through AUTH-012 (12 total)
- Implement: Login page, auth guards, session management
- Test: Authentication flow, redirects, security

### /admin-02-dashboard
Epic 2: CEO Dashboard
- Read: `documentation/admin/02-EPIC-Dashboard.md`
- Stories: DASH-001 through DASH-022 (15 total)
- Implement: Executive dashboard, KPI cards, pod performance table
- Test: Metric calculations, data fetching, real-time updates

### /admin-03-user-management
Epic 3: User Management
- Read: `documentation/admin/03-EPIC-UserManagement.md`
- Stories: USER-001 through USER-018 (18 total)
- Implement: User directory, role management, bulk operations
- Test: User CRUD, search, filtering, bulk actions

### /admin-04-permissions
Epic 4: Permissions & Audit
